 reveal the soul of the city itself.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aNight peoplexNew York (State)xNew YorkxNew York (State)xNew York. 0aNight peoplezNew York (State)zNew York. 0aNight workxNew York (State)xNew York. 0aNight workzNew York (State)zNew York. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aafter dark.  aanthropology.  abrooklyn.  acab drivers.  acity dwellers.  acity life.  acity workers.  acoffee.  acontemporary new york.  acrowded cities.  acultural critique.  aculture.  adelis.  adiners.  afishing boats.  afry cooks.  agraveyard shift.  ahomelessness.  ainterviews.  alife and culture.  amanhattan.  amen and women.  anew york city.  anight life.  anight owls.  anight workers.  anightshift.  anonfiction.  aphotographs.  asocial relationships.  atrain conductors.  aunited states.  aurban life.  aworking at night.1 aSharman, Cheryl Harris, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094206640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520942066423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520942066/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles